[This article mentions that chickens are returning to the markets for sale
and that effective tomorrow EU "member state veterinarians had approved a
single export certificate, which could clear the way for Belgium to restart
shipments of meat and dairy products guaranteed free of dioxin from
Saturday." The details of the criteria for issuing the certificate are not
given. Checking the EU website <http://europa.eu.int> did not produce
further information on this. Provided by MPP. - Mod.TG
